text: Transcript could mean: * Transcript (molecular biology) refers to a strand of messenger RNA * Transcript (education), a copy of a student's permanent academic record * Transcript (medical), the documented medical record of patients * Film Transcript, a transcript needed for dialogue * Transcript (law), a record of all court proceedings * Transcript programming language, a computer programming language * Adobe Transcript, a commercial troff tool from Adobe Systems * The Transcript, Ohio Wesleyan University's student-run newspaper == Related pages == *Transcription (linguistics)
title: Transcript
